records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

AS TO COUNT 1:

Defendant sentenced to serve 100 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 3 (three) days time served.  COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 9 months: If revoked: Huber release privileges for work ONLY:


CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
            
     *   Successfully complete Gun Safety Course.
     *   No contact with victim Darnell H.
     *   No illegal transfer of firearm.
     *   No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause. 
     *   Pay all mandatory costs and surcharges during the 
          period of probation. 
          Any remaining balance at the end of probation will be due  
          immediately or an entry of a civil judgment shall be imposed.
          
 Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Rights; received and filed.

Defendant Jabrian M Moss in court with attorney Torrie R. Williams.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: TC.

AS TO COUNT 1:

Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the criminal complaint and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant further advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.

Defendant Jabrian M Moss in court with attorney Reyna Ivonne Morales. Derrick Waterstreet under the student practice rule supervised by Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: TC. Case calendared for projected guilty plea and sentencing. For reasons stated on the record, Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea and sentencing in Branch 37.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for June 8, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Award from GTS Unlimited Firearms Training Academy on behalf of the defendant; received and filed.   Deputy Court Clerk: TC.
